---
name: devops-update
description: Update Azure DevOps work items - change state, add comments, assign, or bulk close. Use when closing/resolving work after completing tasks, or adding progress comments to tickets.
---

Update Azure DevOps work items for the Charter Hall MSM project.

## Azure DevOps Config

- Org: `https://dev.azure.com/acclt-daas`
- Project: `Charter Hall - MSM Implementation`

## Encoding Note

Always use PowerShell (not bash) to run `az` commands. For queries that return JSON, write to a temp file:

```
powershell.exe -Command "az boards query --wiql \"...\" --org https://dev.azure.com/acclt-daas --project 'Charter Hall - MSM Implementation' | Out-File -Encoding utf8 C:\Users\dinne\AppData\Local\Temp\wi_result.json"
```

## State Rules

Work item types have different valid terminal states — always check type before setting state:

| Type | Done State |
|------|-----------|
| Task | **Closed** |
| User Story | **Resolved** |
| Feature | **Resolved** |
| Bug | **Resolved** |

`az boards work-item update` does NOT take a `--project` flag — use `--org` only.

## Gather Inputs

Before making any changes, confirm with the user:

1. **Which items?** — Work item IDs (single or list)
2. **What action?** — Close/Resolve, add comment, assign, or combination
3. **Comment content?** — What to say, or derive from recent work in the repo

If the user says "mark done" or "close these", look up each item's type first to determine the correct state.

## Fetch Item Type (before updating)

```
powershell.exe -Command "az boards work-item show --id {ID} --org https://dev.azure.com/acclt-daas"
```

Check `fields.System.WorkItemType` in the response.

## Update State and Add Comment

```
powershell.exe -Command "az boards work-item update --id {ID} --state '{state}' --discussion '{comment}' --org https://dev.azure.com/acclt-daas"
```

## Assign to Someone

```
powershell.exe -Command "az boards work-item update --id {ID} --assigned-to '{email}' --org https://dev.azure.com/acclt-daas"
```

